gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Warriors 117, Spurs 113
gameRecap.excerpt: Stephen Curry led Golden State with 33 points, eight assists, and seven 3PM as the Warriors defeated the Spurs, 117-113. Draymond Green (21 points, 11 assists, six rebounds) and Klay Thompson (13 points) added 34 points. Victor Wembanyama led San Antonio with 32 points, nine rebounds, five assists, four steals, and three blocks in the loss. The Warriors have won their fourth consecutive game as they move to 40-34 on the year while the Spurs drop to 18-57.
